    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">von thielmann</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging your note of the 22d
                            instant, I have the pleasure to inform you that your present request has
                            been anticipated by an instruction sent to the consul-general of the
                            United States at Apia, Samoa, under date of June 17 last, wherein he was
                            directed to act in accordance with the propositions contained in Mr.
                            Gresham’s note to you of April 18 last.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
